    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fairer and higher funding per school student",
        "additional_details": "Since 2010 school budgets have been reduced in real terms by 8% (20% at post-16) \r\n-Class sizes are rising \r\n-Often, the most vulnerable students in schools are bearing the brunt of cuts, with schools struggling to provide the levels of support they are entitled to. \r\n\r\nFunding per pupil 2017/18 \r\nLondon \u00a35,872 \r\nSouth West \u00a35,181 \r\nYorkshire and The Humber \u00a35,110 \r\nWest Midlands \u00a35,087 \r\nNorth East \u00a35,029 \r\nEast of England \u00a34,967 \r\nEast Midlands \u00a34,953 \r\nNorth West \u00a34,912 \r\nSouth East \u00a34,832 \r\nCambridgeshire \u00a34528",
        "background": "Schools are still not being provided with adequate funding to deliver the level of provision and support that is expected and that our children deserve.\r\n\r\nWe are facing a funding crisis in our schools. With vast differences in funding per pupil; schools struggling with costs across the UK\r\n",
